ient, allows us to make an extended contribution.  Good damage.  We'll still have to be VERY careful when we use it, as AoE used improperly is instant suicide.  Tell me what you think please.<br>
<br>
Hraveob<br>
gnome nuker extroidinaire of Lanys T`Vyl <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/urochenko.showPublicProfile?language=EN>rochenko</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/29/01 3:12 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rain Spells</span><hr size=1> Also, this would fix all lvls, not just lvl 60.  Definately a bonus.  <br>
Hraveob <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utehutibloodstorm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tehuti Bloodstorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 30<br> <font color=#ffffff>(3/31/01 8:13 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rain Spells</span><hr size=1> I wish our rain spells would stick to a mob, they were great when root worked. Very mana efficient. However now.... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :/ --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/ohwell.gif ALT=":/"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>"I learned that it is the weak who are cruel, and that 
